<P>Parental Wishes and Charges. OR, THE ENJOYMENT of a Glorious Christ, Proposed, as the Great BLESSED|NESS, which Christian PARENTS desire, both for <HI>Themselves,</HI> and for their CHILDREN. In a DISCOURSE, now put into the Hands of such PARENTS, as would be Assisted in their Duty, by putting such Things into the Hands of their CHILDREN.</P>
<P>CHRISTUS <HI>noster Amor,</HI> CHRISTUS que Honor, Omnia CHRISTUS.</P>
<P><HI>Boston,</HI> in <HI>N. E.</HI> Printed and Sold by <HI>Timothy Green,</HI> 1705.</P>
</DIV1>
